# LENGOLF Booking System

A comprehensive booking system for LENGOLF that leverages Google APIs, Redis caching, and LINE notifications to manage and confirm bookings efficiently.

## Table of Contents

- [Features](#features)
- [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
- [Prerequisites](#prerequisites)
- [Setup Instructions](#setup-instructions)
- [Environment Variables](#environment-variables)
- [Running the Application](#running-the-application)
- [Project Structure](#project-structure)
- [Logging](#logging)
- [Contributing](#contributing)
- [License](#license)

## Features

- **User Authentication:** Users can sign in using Google Sign-In.
- **Booking Management:** View and book available slots based on real-time availability.
- **Caching:** Utilizes Redis to cache available slots, enhancing performance.
- **Notifications:** Sends booking confirmations via LINE Notify.
- **Logging:** Implements structured logging using Winston for error tracking and monitoring.

## Technologies Used

- **Backend:** Node.js, Express.js
- **Authentication:** Google OAuth 2.0
- **Caching:** Redis
- **APIs:** Google Calendar API, Google Sheets API
- **Notifications:** LINE Notify API
- **Logging:** Winston
- **Scheduling:** node-cron
- **Date Handling:** Luxon
- **Frontend:** HTML, CSS (Bootstrap), JavaScript

## Prerequisites

- **Node.js:** Ensure you have Node.js (v14 or higher) installed. [Download Node.js](https://nodejs.org/)
- **Redis:** A running Redis instance. [Install Redis](https://redis.io/download)
- **Google Cloud Account:** For accessing Google APIs.
- **LINE Notify Token:** For sending notifications.

